<promed@promedmail.org>

[The article mentions the horse was euthanized but does not tell us
what happened to the sentinel chicken. In all likelihood the chicken
died of the disease as birds tend to be sensitive to the encephalitis
diseases. This includes such birds as emus and ostriches as well.

Horses should be vaccinated against the disease. A single injection
contains protection against EEE and WNV. Both diseases are
transmitted from the mosquito. The disease cannot be transmitted to
humans by birds or horses but rather through the mosquito. - Mod.TG]
